### Static Members

Static members belong to the class itself, not to instances. They are accessed using the class name.

```dart
class MathUtils {
  static const double pi = 3.14159;

  static int add(int a, int b) => a + b;

  static double circleArea(double radius) => pi * radius * radius;
}

void main() {
  print(MathUtils.pi); // 3.14159
  print(MathUtils.add(5, 3)); // 8
  print(MathUtils.circleArea(10)); // 314.159
}
```

### Static Fields

```dart
class Counter {
  static int _count = 0;

  Counter() {
    _count++;
  }

  static int get count => _count;

  static void reset() => _count = 0;
}

void main() {
  var c1 = Counter();
  var c2 = Counter();
  var c3 = Counter();

  print(Counter.count); // 3
  Counter.reset();
  print(Counter.count); // 0
}
```

### Static Methods

```dart
class StringUtils {
  static String capitalize(String text) {
    if (text.isEmpty) return text;
    return text[0].toUpperCase() + text.substring(1);
  }

  static bool isPalindrome(String text) {
    var clean = text.toLowerCase().replaceAll(' ', '');
    return clean == clean.split('').reversed.join();
  }

  static String truncate(String text, int maxLength) {
    if (text.length <= maxLength) return text;
    return '${text.substring(0, maxLength)}...';
  }
}

void main() {
  print(StringUtils.capitalize('hello')); // Hello
  print(StringUtils.isPalindrome('racecar')); // true
  print(StringUtils.truncate('Long text here', 4)); // Long...
}
```

### Static vs Instance Members

| Aspect | Static | Instance |
|--------|--------|----------|
| Belongs to | Class | Object |
| Access | `ClassName.member` | `object.member` |
| Memory | One per class | One per instance |
| `this` access | No | Yes |
| Override | No | Yes |

### Static Initialization

```dart
class Config {
  static final String appName = 'DartApp';
  static final String version = '1.0.0';
  static final Map<String, String> defaults = {
    'theme': 'light',
    'language': 'en',
  };

  static void printConfig() {
    print('$appName v$version');
    print('Defaults: $defaults');
  }
}
```

> **Key Point:** Use `static` for utility methods and class-level constants. Static methods cannot access instance members because they have no `this` reference.

codeExample:
class Employee {
  final String name;
  final double salary;

  static const double taxRate = 0.2;
  static int _totalEmployees = 0;

  Employee(this.name, this.salary) {
    _totalEmployees++;
  }

  double get netSalary => salary * (1 - taxRate);

  static int get totalEmployees => _totalEmployees;

  static double calculateAnnualCost(List<Employee> employees) {
    return employees.fold(0.0, (sum, e) => sum + e.salary);
  }
}

void main() {
  var e1 = Employee('Alice', 50000);
  var e2 = Employee('Bob', 60000);

  print('Total employees: ${Employee.totalEmployees}');
  print('${e1.name} net: \$${e1.netSalary}');
  print('Annual cost: \$${Employee.calculateAnnualCost([e1, e2])}');
}
